\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. S. tenuifolia} Schrader, {\i Fl. Germ.} 272 (1806). Stems usually 20-30 cm. Leaves 0·4-0·6(-3) mm wide, usually junciform or setaceous, pruinose and more or less hairy above; sheaths usually glabrous, the basal reticulate. Inflorescence (10-)15(-30) mm. Glumes c. 4 mm, lanceolate to ovate, acute or acuminate. Lemma 4-5 mm, blue or grey, sparsely ciliate, with 1-3 awns up to 1·5 mm. Palea longer than lemma, ciliate on the keels.{\i  Limestone rocks. • Italy, W. Jugoslavia, N. Albania.} Al It Ju.
\par

