\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. S. heuflerana} Schur,{\i  Verh. Zool.-Bot. Ges. Wien }{\b 6}: 203 (1856). Stems up to 70 cm. Leaves 2-3(-7) mm wide, strongly pruinose above when young, the uppermost 1·5-3(-5) cm; sheaths glabrous. Inflorescence usually 10-30 × 7-11 mm. Glumes usually 3·5-4·5 mm, narrowly lanceolate, sparsely ciliate; awn 0·5-2·5 mm. Lemma pubescent; awns (1-)2(-4) mm. Palea with awns up to 2 mm.{\i  Woods and rocks; calcicole. • E.C. Europe.} Cz Hu Rm Rs (W).
\par

