\pard\f0\fs28    ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b heuflerana}: Laxly caespitose. Leaves flat or convolute, rarely folded. Glumes up to 4·5 mm. Lemma and palea up to 4·5 mm. 2n = 28.{\i  Throughout the range of the species}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28    ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b hungarica} (Ujhelyi) Deyl, {\i Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  76}: 364 (1978) ({\i S. hungarica} Ujhelyi): Densely caespitose. Leaves flat or folded. Glumes up to 6 mm. Lemma 5 mm. Palea 5-6 mm. 2n = 56.{\i  Czechoslovakia and Hungary}.
