\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 9. S. bielzii} Schur,{\i  Verh. Mitt. Siebenb. Ver. Naturw.}{\b  1}: 109 (1850). Stems rather stout. Leaves 1·5-2·5 mm wide, flat or convolute, the uppermost 2-3 cm; sheaths glabrous. Inflorescence (11-)16(-30) × 7-10 mm, the bracts at its base ovate to lanceolate. Glumes 4-10 mm, ovate-lanceolate, ciliate; awn up to 4 mm. Lemma 4-5 mm, hairy; middle awn 2-3 mm, the laterals 0·5-1 mm. Palea (3-)4(-6) mm, hairy, unawned or with awns up to 0·5 mm. 2n = 56. {\i Stony or grassy slopes. • Carpathians and mountains of Balkan peninsula.} Bu Gr Ju Rm Rs (W).
