\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 10. S. coerulans} Friv.,{\i  Flora }({\i Regensb}.){\b  19}: 438 (1836) (incl. {\i S. orbelica} (Velen.) Hayek). Stems up to 25 cm, stout. Leaves 2-4 mm wide, glabrous, usually plicate, the uppermost 1-3 cm; sheaths densely villous. Inflorescence 15-20 × 8-12 mm, dense, the bracts at its base conspicuous, rounded. Glumes 4-7 mm, ciliate; awn (1-)2(-3) mm. Lemma 4·5-5 mm, villous; middle awn 3-4 mm, the laterals 1-2 mm. Palea longer than lemma; awns 1-2 mm. 2n = 56.{\i  Stony or grassy slopes. • Mountains of Balkan peninsula; S. Carpathians. }Al Bu Gr Ju Rm.
\par

